<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10275952>
    dc:description "FIGURES 54–61. Neobisium (N.) leolatellai n. sp., male paratype, Grotta della Cava, 17.VII.2010 (Bassiano, Latium) (unless otherwise stated). 54, epistome of carapace and right ocular area; 55, right chelicera, dorsal view; 56, female paratype, same data: movable finger of right chelicera, dorsal view; 57, anterior processes of right coxa I; 58, trochanter, femur and patella of right pedipalp, dorsal view; 59, right pedipalpal chela, dorsal view; 60, same, antiaxial view, with magnified details of teeth; 61, right leg IV, antiaxial view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10275952/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10275954>
    dc:description "FIGURES 62–63. Neobisium (N.) leolatellai n. sp. tritonymph paratype, Grotta della Cava, 17.VII.2010 (Bassiano, Latium). 62, epistome of carapace and right ocular area; 63, id., fixed finger apices of right chela (left) with abnormal position of trichobotrium it and of left chela (right) with normal position of it." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10275954/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10275970>
    dc:description "FIGURE 119. Map depicting known distribution of Neobisum species with troglomorphic facies from central and southern Italy." ;
